Hungary’s OTP Bank May Acquire Croatia’s Karlovacka, Banka Says

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-03-24T08:58:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/hungary-s-otp-bank-may-acquire-croatia-s-karlovacka-banka-says.html
Hungary’s OTP Bank is interested in
acquiring  Croatia ’s Karlovacka Banka and is conducting due
diligence,  Banka Magazine  said, citing people it didn’t
identify.  The eighth biggest bank in Croatia, OTP said its management
will move forward with the deal if its examination of Karlovacka
shows no problems, according to the Zagreb-based magazine today.  Karlovacka, which has a market value of 87 million kuna
($16.5 million), reported a loss of 83 million kuna in 2010,
according to the magazine. The Hungarian bank has a retail
network of 99 offices in Croatia, while Karlovacka has 18, Banka
reported, citing the banks’ websites.  To contact the reporter on this story: Jasmina Kuzmanovic at
   jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  